<h2>The weather in January 2020</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
Temperatures in January 2020 were above the 1981-2010 average over most of Europe. The European-average temperature for January 2020 was 3.1&deg;C warmer than the average January in the period 1981-2010. They were exceptionally high for the time of year in the north and east, in a band spreading eastward and south-eastward from Norway to Russia, with values more than 6&deg;C above average in many places. Norway experienced its warmest January day on record early in the month, and the month was the second warmest since 1900 for the country as a whole. Observing stations in central and southern Finland recorded their warmest January in the period since at least 1961.
In large parts of the Balkans and Hungary and some parts of southern Europe temperatures were little below average.
