<h3>Radiation and Cloudiness</h3>
In January it was less cloudy than normal in large parts of Europe, especially the southeastern part, corresponding to a positive anomaly in incoming radiation and a negative anomaly in cloud cover (resp figure 14 and 15). Parts of Scandinavia, the Netherlands and Spain experienced more cloudy than normal conditions and thus a deficit in radiation.
